data.title: Famous Faces From Woodstock, GA
data.meta_description: From Oscar-winning actors to top-selling musicians, Woodstock, GA has produced some of the most famous faces in entertainment.
data.text:
Being a predominantly residential community located just outside Georgia’s capital, Woodstock is home to a long list of very popular neighborhoods. In recent years, the city has gained a reputation as one of the best places to visit in Metro Atlanta.

Why Do People Love Woodstock, GA?

Apart from the beautiful attractions and the small-town charm, the city of Woodstock also boasts of having produced some of the best annual events in Woodstock and some very influential people throughout its history. Below is a list of famous people who have, at some point, lived in the city of Woodstock, GA:

Marcus Alexander Bagwell

Bagwell, also known by the ring name Buff Bagwell, is a prominent professional wrestler who doubles up as an actor. Bagwell has worked with several major wrestling promotions including the now-defunct World Championship Wrestling, World Wrestling Federation, and Total Nonstop Action Wrestling. However, most of his success came during his time with World Championship Wrestling where he won the World Tag Team Championship five times. Originally from Marietta, Bagwell currently lives in Woodstock.

Christopher Brandon Kirk

Kirk is a famous American pro golfer who was born in Tennessee and raised in the city of Woodstock, Georgia. A four-time PGA Tour winner, Kirk was one of the highest-ranking golfers in the world in 2015 with a career-high of 16. He has since relocated to the city of Athens, Georgia where he lives with his wife.

Dimitri Leslie Roger

Roger is a New York-born rapper who is currently contracted to Republic Records. Popularly known by stage name Rich the Kid, Roger spent most of his childhood in Woodstock after his parents divorced and his mother moved to Georgia. Apart from being an accomplished rapper, he is also the founder and CEO of the high-flying Rich Forever Music label. Roger currently resides in Atlanta City.

Chandler Riggs

Riggs is a sensational young actor from Woodstock, GA, who rose to fame in 2010 after landing a well-deserved role as Carl Grimes on AMC’s horror movie- The Walking Dead. Riggs has also featured in several other critically acclaimed films including the likes of Inherit the Viper, Mercy, and A Million Little Things.

Other famous residents and former residents of this beautiful southern city include baseball superstar Nicholas William Markakis, award-winning author Mary Hood, football quarterback Buster Skrine, and David Dean Rusk who served as United States Secretary of State under both Presidents John F. Kennedy and his successor Lyndon B. Johnson.
